'''Tracey Forbes''' is a [[Canadian]] [[television writer]] and [[television producer|producer]]. She has worked on numerous Canadian and American television shows including ''[[Flashpoint (TV series)|Flashpoint]]'', ''[[The Bridge (Canadian TV series)|The Bridge]]'', ''[[Spider-Man: The New Animated Series]]'' and ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer (TV series)|Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]''. In 2012/2013, she co-created, wrote and executive produced the TV drama series "[[Cracked (Canadian TV series)|Cracked]]" on CBC in Canada.
Forbes also wrote the made-for-TV movie ''[[Booky's Crush]]'' in 2009, based on the Booky novels by [[Bernice Thurman Hunter]], and ''Girlfriend in a Coma'' based on Douglas Coupland's novel.{{citation needed|date=November 2013}}
